{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Plan refinement after PASS advisories: implement direct adapter composition, not the unused language-dispatch table. Add a per-command  dict to the metrics evaluation context; its lifecycle is exactly one  invocation (no module/global state). A focused cache helper keys by producer name plus immutable repo root/scan-root inputs and stores both AnalyzerResult and Unavailable, so each of scc/lizard/jscpd executes at most once in that context. Rework the existing scc specs to read this cache, and register structural/high-confidence  and  specs that expose the adapters' normalized payloads or preserve Unavailable as registry Unavailable. If ANALYZERS/resolve_analyzer/analyze_or_unavailable remain unused after this direct composition, remove that dead dispatch while retaining AnalyzerResult/Analyzer protocol compatibility. Prove deduplication with a unit call-count test that evaluates both scc-backed specs in one context and asserts one scc invocation; separately assert one call and exact payload/Unavailable propagation for lizard and jscpd. Add interface tests through  for value and missing-producer output. Adapter-level nonzero/malformed handling is already pinned by 21fb/3ba0 tests and will be retained, not duplicated. This per-context design is chosen over lru_cache/module state to avoid stale cross-command and cross-test results."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784858030967009001,"uuid":"4f354415-32cc-46fb-9d7a-df24db521d37"}